race.comment: RHINESTONE RORY (3) is a 30-start maiden who just can't seem to get off the mark but has been going along well. Last start raced on speed for a good fourth at Horsham and finds a much lesser race here. Trip suits, will stalk the pace and gets a chance. HAYAI TSURU (4) was fair fresh over 1500m on slow going but strips much fitter and will relish the extra ground. Jockey has a strong strike-rate with the yard and looks one of the better chances. PLASTIC DREAMS (1) has been on speed and being grabbed late, the latest when beaten four lengths in a tougher maiden. Has pace and will take catching from the low draw. Worth noting trainer has only had two starters at this track for two wins. MISS SOLAR HART (6) was placed two back then safely held last time in the same race as PLASTIC DREAMS. Best figures measure up and is one of the main hopes with even luck.  PROUD CHIEF (2) wasn't far from the winner last time and rates a chance on that figure.
